article.headline: McNeese St. 24, Northwestern St. 7
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- Jacob Bower ran for a touchdown and threw for another as McNeese State rallied to defeat Northwestern State 24-7 on Saturday. The Cowboys (2-2, 1-0 Southland Conference) trailed 7-0 before a pass by Northwestern State's Tyler Wolfe from the McNeese 19 was intercepted by Kentrel Butler. Bower capped McNeese's 12-play, 64-yard drive on the ensuing possession with a 1-yard touchdown run. Bower, who was 19-for-25 passing for 233 yards, gave the Cowboys a 17-7 lead on a 21-yard pass to Marcus Wiltz with 9:50 left in the fourth quarter. The Demons (1-4, 0-1) took the lead on Wolfe's 15-yard pass to Adrian Reese with 11:35 left in the first quarter. Josh Lewis 23-yard field goal gave the Cowboys the lead for good with 5:32 left in the third. Wolfe finished with 194 yards and two interceptions on 16-for-24 passing.
